text:
W. 125th Street, east from Lenox Avenue. To the right is the Marion Building, at the S.W. corner of this point. The Harlem Branch of the Chatham Phenix National Bank is on the north side of this thoroughfare and east of the Avenue. In the far background is the Lee Building, located at the N.E. corner of Park Avenue and W. 125th Street. The automobiles in the foreground obstruct a clear view of the N.Y.C.R.R. elevated tracks and station at that point.

May 1928.

Geo. L. Balgue

The structures at the N.E. corner of Lenox Avenue and W. 125th Street. Note at the right the bank building occupied at this date by the Manufacturers Trust Co.

July 28, 1932.

P.L. Sperr

text:
Street Scene--Manhattan: The news stand at the corner of Lenox Avenue and W. 125th Street in Harlem.

January 1938

Alexander Alland

This is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portrait of N. Y." by Felix Reisenberg and Alex. Alland, IRGV.
title: Street scenes - Newsstands.
